<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>An information disclosure vulnerability was discovered in the Service
Discovery Protocol (SDP) in bluetoothd, allowing a proximate attacker to
obtain sensitive information from bluetoothd process memory, including
Bluetooth encryption keys.</p>

<p>For the oldstable distribution (jessie), this problem has been fixed
in version 5.23-2+deb8u1.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (stretch), this problem has been fixed in
version 5.43-2+deb9u1.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your bluez packages.</p>
</define-tag>

